node.text:
The amazing part about our growth is that every day we learn about each other. There are many things we wish we could change about ourselves , but being in a relationship means we want to do it together and never apart. I am “California sober” and have been for almost 7 months now, I have become pescatarian for about the same amount of time and we pray about 3-2 times a day, for almost 7 months also. Having the right partner can propel your growth because we find each other accountable (I sometimes forget to pray before we eat and immediately I look at him and he says ‘that’s between you and him’ and I have found myself feeling even guilty for not thanking the man upstairs for food and health. I also used to go to church on Sunday’s’ and I felt the “restart” button for the rest of my week, now I have the same feeling but at least once a day. I’m constantly working on myself, I seek for elevation in every aspect of my life. My prayers were not to find a man who loved me dearly but instead a partner who respected me,  a team player who would could help me achieve my daily goals. The love is always there but love isn’t the only ingredient in a relationship; the main things are loyalty and respect. Now that I’ve been granted my manifestation, I have to nurture it, feed it, water it , trim it when it’s off, give it light when it gets dark. I never want to yell, I never want to curse, I always want to give my partner peace and now that it is how I plan to keep it forever.
I love you Fetaiaki 💕.

We opened our first branch of @needflowercom  in Miami . Please follow @needflowerMIA for updates .
Can’t wait for our next project!!!!
I LOVE YOUUUUU SO MUCH MI REY 💕
📸 @ariaswellness89

node.text: Even in times of darkness, memories of small kindnesses bring light. The bond I have with the ocean 🌊 is great, the nature grounds me and cleanses me. I love going to the water and get in deep thought of my sorrows and happy times, “she” hears it all as she responds to me loud and clear.
